"index_reference": "4627: creatures",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Generally, living beings within God's creation, especially the exotic animals seen in visions, which often have a deep symbolic significance.</p>\n<h2>Creatures representing angelic beings who worship God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek1:5-Ezek1:6\">EZK 1:5–1:6</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev4:6-Rev4:8\">REV 4:6–4:8</a></strong> <em>The strange creatures of Ezekiel and Revelation seem to stand for the fulness and variety of God's creation.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek1:7-Ezek1:25\">EZK 1:7–1:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek3:12-Ezek3:13\">EZK 3:12–3:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek10:15-Ezek10:22\">EZK 10:15–10:22</a> <em>The creatures are here identified as cherubim</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev4:9-Rev4:11\">REV 4:9–4:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev5:6-Rev5:14\">REV 5:6–5:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev6:1-Rev6:3\">REV 6:1–6:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev6:5-Rev6:6\">REV 6:5–6:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev7:11\">REV 7:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev14:3\">REV 14:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev15:7\">REV 15:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev19:4\">REV 19:4</a></p>\n<h2>Creatures representing kings or kingdoms</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:17\">DAN 7:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan8:20-Dan8:21\">DAN 8:20–8:21</a></strong> <em>The “beasts” here are unnatural, and represent the hostility of human empires to the rule of God. The horns represent individual kings within an imperial dynasty.</em></p>\n<h2>Creatures representing Satan</h2>\n<p>The beast here represents Satan, with the horns representing royal authority at a time of Roman persecution of the church:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev12:3-Rev12:4\">REV 12:3–12:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev12:7-Rev12:9\">REV 12:7–12:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev13:1\">REV 13:1</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:2-Dan7:8\">DAN 7:2–7:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:19-Dan7:26\">DAN 7:19–7:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan8:3-Dan8:12\">DAN 8:3–8:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev11:7\">REV 11:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev13:2-Rev13:8\">REV 13:2–13:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev13:11-Rev13:18\">REV 13:11–13:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev17:3\">REV 17:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev17:7-Rev17:13\">REV 17:7–17:13</a></p>",
